title: College Prep Test Scores
question_text: Suppose $500$ females at a local high school took a college prep test this year. Below is the five-number summary of their scores: Minimum: $14$ First quartile: $16$ Median: $21$ Third quartile: $28$ Maximum: $36$ Which of the following statements is true?

choices.text: About 250 250 females at this high school scored greater than 28 28 .
This is a fairly symmetric distribution.
The student who scored 36 36 is obviously an outlier.
